$8ˆc<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";O:8:"stdClass":24:{s:2:"ID";i:32;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"3";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2022-06-03 05:07:02";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2022-06-03 05:07:02";s:12:"post_content";s:11773:"[et_pb_section fb_built="1" fullwidth="on" _builder_version="4.17.4" _module_preset="default" global_colors_info="{}"][et_pb_fullwidth_header title=" Allergy Management: Get assistance immediately!" subhead="Call 97462 22668 now" button_one_text="Call Directly from Mobile" button_one_url="tel:9746222668" _builder_version="4.17.6" _module_preset="default" title_font="Francois One|700|||||||" title_text_color="#FFFFFF" title_font_size="40px" subhead_font="Francois One|700|||||||" subhead_font_size="30px" subhead_line_height="1.8em" background_enable_color="off" use_background_color_gradient="on" background_color_gradient_stops="rgba(0,0,0,0.13) 0%|rgba(0,0,0,0.62) 100%" background_color_gradient_overlays_image="on" background_image="https://www.allergytest.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/BANNER-1.jpeg" custom_button_one="on" button_one_text_color="#FFFFFF" button_one_bg_color="#ff4100" button_one_border_width="0px" button_one_font="Dosis|500|||||||" custom_padding="152px||152px||true|" title_font_size_tablet="40px" title_font_size_phone="30px" title_font_size_last_edited="on|phone" subhead_font_size_tablet="30px" subhead_font_size_phone="25px" subhead_font_size_last_edited="on|phone" global_colors_info="{}"][/et_pb_fullwidth_header][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built="1" _builder_version="4.17.6" _module_preset="default" background_image="https://www.allergytest.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/home-image_1.png" parallax="on" parallax_method="off" custom_padding="63px||63px||true|" global_colors_info="{}"][et_pb_row column_structure="1_4,3_4" _builder_version="4.17.4" _module_preset="default" global_colors_info="{}"][et_pb_column type="1_4" _builder_version="4.17.4" _module_preset="default" global_colors_info="{}"][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="3_4" _builder_version="4.17.4" _module_preset="default" global_colors_info="{}"][et_pb_text _builder_version="4.17.4" _module_preset="default" header_font="Francois One|700|||||||" header_text_color="#000000" header_font_size="35px" header_line_height="1.3em" custom_margin="||8px|||" header_font_size_tablet="35px" header_font_size_phone="25px" header_font_size_last_edited="on|phone" global_colors_info="{}"]<h1 class="mbr-fonts-style mbr-title align-left pb-3 display-2"><strong>ALLERGY</strong></h1>[/et_pb_text][et_pb_text _builder_version="4.17.4" _module_preset="default" text_font="Dosis||||||||" text_text_color="#000000" text_font_size="16px" text_line_height="1.8em" global_colors_info="{}"]<p style="text-align: justify;"><span>Allergy problems have a solution now.</span><br /><span>Allergy is experienced by all at one time or other,mild or severe. Only when it is severe we consider it seriously and take action.</span><br /><span>Allergy symptoms range from making you miserable to putting you at risk for life-threatening reactions.</span><br /><span>According to the leading experts in allergy, an allergic reaction begins in the immune system. Our immune system protects us from invading organisms that can cause illness. If you have an allergy, your immune system mistakes an otherwise harmless substance as an invader. The substance is called an allergen. The immune system overreacts to the allergen by producing Immunoglobulin E (IgE) antibodies. These antibodies travel to cells that release histamine and other chemicals, causing an allergic reaction.</span><br /><strong>Symptoms</strong><br /><span>All allergic reactions typically triggers symptoms in the nose,lungs,throat,sinuses,ears,lining of the stomach or on the skin. For some people, allergies can also trigger symptoms of asthma. In the most serious cases, a life-threatening reaction called anaphylaxis can occur.</span><br /><span>A number of different allergens are responsible for allergic reactions.</span><br /><span>The most common includes:</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Dust</strong></li>
<li style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Food</strong></li>
<li style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Insect stings</strong></li>
<li style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Animal dander</strong></li>
</ol>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span>What most people do not know is that many of the normal foods which we consider natural or healthy can turn as an allergen for a person. Many people are diagnosed having allergic to common foods such as milk, bananas, wheat, yeast, melons, dal, egg, lemon, ladies finger etc.</span><br /><span>Consuming foods that is allergic to one increases their IgE levels which triggers antibodies causing allergic reaction.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Children and Allergies<br /></strong><span>Any child can develop allergies, but they are more common children from families with a history of allergies. Since itâ€™s impossible for parents to control absolutely everything that their child is exposed to or eats, parents should instead focus on monitoring their child for symptoms.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span>Â Early identification of childhood allergies will improve your childâ€™s quality of life, reduce the number of missed school days and help you avoid having to use sick time or vacation days to care for your child. If your son or daughter is struggling, take control of the situation and take a test today.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Allergy Symptoms in Children</strong></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: justify;"><span>Skin rashes or hives (atopic dermatitis or eczema)</span></li>
<li style="text-align: justify;"><span>Difficulty breathing (asthma)</span></li>
<li style="text-align: justify;"><span>Sneezing, coughing, a runny nose or itchy eyes</span></li>
<li style="text-align: justify;"><span>Stomach upset.</span></li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Common Allergy triggers in Children</strong></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: justify;"><span>Outdoors: tree pollen, plant pollen, insect bites or stings.</span></li>
<li style="text-align: justify;"><span>Indoors: pet or animal hair or fur, dust mites.</span></li>
<li style="text-align: justify;"><span>Irritants: cigarette smoke, perfume, car exhaust.</span></li>
<li style="text-align: justify;"><span>Foods: peanuts, eggs, milk and milk products.</span></li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Allergy Diagnosis</strong><span></span><br /><span>There are no treatment for allergies. Medication can control difficult situations and is a must when the cause is not identified.</span><br /><span>Identifying the cause and then managing the triggers are the best way to solve allergy issues.</span><br /><span>The most modern method available now is by analizing the blood against a package of potential allergens. Usually the results come up as a few items of high allergy, some medium and some mild. Managing the identified items can completely bring down the allergies and thus having peace with your body.</span><br /><span>PREVENTIVE CARE LAB is engaged in helping people discover the harmful subjects that can affect a persons body by way of a single blood test.</span><br /><span>Thousands of customers who have been living with serious allergy conditions for several years were able to use their services and now happily living without the concerns of allergy.</span><br /><span>A comprehensive test for foods, inhalants and contact items is ideal to identify the causes.</span></p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built="1" module_id="2" module_class="2" _builder_version="4.17.6" _module_preset="default" use_background_color_gradient="on" background_color_gradient_stops="rgba(255,255,255,0.7) 0%|rgba(255,255,255,0.59) 99%" background_color_gradient_overlays_image="on" background_image="https://www.allergytest.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/row-bgimg-1.jpeg" parallax="on" parallax_method="off" global_colors_info="{}"][et_pb_row _builder_version="4.17.4" _module_preset="default" global_colors_info="{}"][et_pb_column type="4_4" _builder_version="4.17.4" _module_preset="default" global_colors_info="{}"][et_pb_text _builder_version="4.18.0" _module_preset="default" header_font="Francois One|700|||||||" header_text_color="#000000" header_font_size="35px" header_letter_spacing="1px" header_line_height